// Figure 3.7: Micro-Frontend Runtime Composition
// Sequence: Browser → Host → Router → Registry → Remote → Inject

// ==================== ACTORS (left to right) ====================
Browser [icon: chrome, color: blue]
Host Shell [icon: react, color: green]
Router [icon: git-branch, color: orange]
Registry [icon: list, color: purple]
Remote MFE [icon: package, color: cyan]
Fallback [icon: alert-circle, color: red]

// ==================== SUCCESS PATH ====================
// 1. User navigates
Browser > Host Shell : Navigate to /store/*

// 2. Host matches route
Host Shell > Router : routes.tsx

// 3. Router checks registry
Router > Registry : getMicroFrontendConfig(store)

// 4. Registry returns config
Registry > Remote MFE : Fetch remoteEntry.js

// 5. Remote injects into Host
Remote MFE > Host Shell : inject(containerId, config)

// ==================== PROTECTED PATH ====================
// For /checkout/* and /account/*
Router > Router : ProtectedRoute check
Router > Registry : If auth OK

// ==================== FAILURE PATH ====================
Registry > Fallback : Remote unavailable
Fallback > Host Shell : ErrorBoundaryFallback
